messages.content:
“Yena kodhena kuddhāse,
sattā gacchanti duggatiṁ;
Taṁ kodhaṁ sammadaññāya,
pajahanti vipassino;
Pahāya na punāyanti,
imaṁ lokaṁ kudācanan”ti.

"When overcome by anger,
beings go to a bad destination;
Completely comprehending anger,
those with insight abandon it;
Having abandoned it, they do not come again,
to this world at any time."

Tasmā hi ne namasseyya,
sakkareyya ca paṇḍito;
Annena atha pānena,
vatthena sayanena ca;
Ucchādanena nhāpanena,
pādānaṁ dhovanena ca.

Therefore, one should honor them,
and a wise person should respect them;
With food and drink,
with clothing and bedding;
By massaging and by bathing,
and by washing their feet.

Assaddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā dukkathā;
dussīlassa sīlakathā dukkathā;
appassutassa bāhusaccakathā dukkathā;
maccharissa cāgakathā dukkathā;
duppaññassa paññākathā dukkathā.

For the faithless, bhikkhus, talk of faith is difficult;
for the immoral, talk of morality is difficult;
for the less learned, talk of much learning is difficult;
for the stingy, talk of generosity is difficult;
for the unwise, talk of wisdom is difficult.

Saddhassa, bhikkhave, saddhākathā sukathā;
sīlavato sīlakathā sukathā;
bahussutassa bāhusaccakathā sukathā;
cāgavato cāgakathā sukathā;
paññavato paññākathā sukathā.

For the faithful, bhikkhus, talk of faith is pleasant;
for the virtuous, talk of morality is pleasant;
for the well-learned, talk of much learning is pleasant;
for the generous, talk of generosity is pleasant;
for the wise, talk of wisdom is pleasant.

Pamādaṁ appamādena,
yadā nudati paṇḍito;
Paññāpāsādamāruyha,
asoko sokiniṁ pajaṁ;
Pabbataṭṭhova bhūmaṭṭhe,
dhīro bāle avekkhati.

When with heedfulness,
the wise one dispels carelessness;
Climbing the tower of wisdom,
free from sorrow, seeing the sorrowful people;
Like one on a mountain top sees those on the ground,
the wise one sees the immature, unwise people.

“Yena mohena mūḷhāse,
sattā gacchanti duggatiṁ;
Taṁ mohaṁ sammadaññāya,
pajahanti vipassino;
Pahāya na punāyanti,
imaṁ lokaṁ kudācanan”ti.

"When overcome by delusion,
beings go to a bad destination;
Completely comprehending delusion,
those with insight abandon it;
Having abandoned it, they do not come again,
to this world at any time."

“Yena lobhena luddhāse,
sattā gacchanti duggatiṁ;
Taṁ lobhaṁ sammadaññāya,
pajahanti vipassino;
Pahāya na punāyanti,
imaṁ lokaṁ kudācanan”ti.

"When overcome by greed,
beings go to a bad destination;
Completely comprehending greed,
those with insight abandon it;
Having abandoned it, they do not come again,
to this world at any time."

Tamed, he is the best of those who tame;
calm, he is the sage of those who calm;
Freed, he is the foremost of those who free;
crossed over, he is the best of those who cross over.

Manopubbaṅgamā dhammā,
manoseṭṭhā manomayā;
Manasā ce paduṭṭhena,
bhāsati vā karoti vā;
Tato naṁ dukkhamanveti,
cakkaṁva vahato padaṁ.

Mind precedes all mental states.
Mind is their chief, they are all mind-made;
If with a corrupted mind,
one speaks or acts;
discontentment follows them,
like the wheel that follows the foot of the ox.

Manopubbaṅgamā dhammā,
manoseṭṭhā manomayā;
Manasā ce pasannena,
bhāsati vā karoti vā;
Tato naṁ sukhamanveti,
chāyāva anapāyinī.

Mind precedes all mental states,
mind is their chief; they are all mind-made;
If with a clear mind,
one speaks or acts;
happiness follows them,
like a never-departing shadow.

Subhānupassiṁ viharantaṁ,
indriyesu asaṁvutaṁ;
Bhojanamhi cāmattaññuṁ,
kusītaṁ hīnavīriyaṁ;
Taṁ ve pasahati māro,
vāto rukkhaṁva dubbalaṁ.

Living perceiving the attractive,
unrestrained in the senses;
Not knowing moderation in eating,
with laziness and little effort;
Māra indeed overcomes that one,
like the wind overcomes a weak tree.

Asubhānupassiṁ viharantaṁ,
Indriyesu susaṁvutaṁ;
Bhojanamhi ca mattaññuṁ,
Saddhaṁ āraddhavīriyaṁ;
Taṁ ve nappasahati māro,
Vāto selaṁva pabbataṁ.

Living perceiving the unattractive,
well-restrained in the senses;
Knowing moderation in eating,
with faith and strong effort;
Māra indeed does not overcome that one,
like the wind does not overcome a mountain rock.

Appampi ce saṁhita bhāsamāno,
Dhammassa hoti anudhammacārī;
Rāgañca dosañca pahāya mohaṁ,
Sammappajāno suvimuttacitto;
Anupādiyāno idha vā huraṁ vā,
Sa bhāgavā sāmaññassa hoti.

“Sekho asekho ca imasmiṁ loke,
Āhuneyyā yajamānānaṁ honti;
Te ujjubhūtā kāyena,
Vācāya uda cetasā;
Khettaṁ taṁ yajamānānaṁ,
Ettha dinnaṁ mahapphalan”ti.

"The trainee and the arahant in this world,
Are worthy of offerings from those who make offerings;
They are upright in body,
in speech, and in mind;
That field for those who make offerings
Gives great fruit."

“Dve khandhā taññeva siyaṁ,
adhivacanañca hetunā;
Sakkāyena duve vuttā,
assādaviññāṇakena ca;
Ete dasavidhā vuttā,
hoti bhikkhu pucchāyā”ti.

“Sārattā kāmabhogesu,
giddhā kāmesu mucchitā;
Atisāraṁ na bujjhanti,
migā kūṭaṁva oḍḍitaṁ;
Pacchāsaṁ kaṭukaṁ hoti,
vipāko hissa pāpako”ti.

"Enamoured by sensual pleasures,
Greedy, infatuated with desires;
They do not realize they have gone too far,
Like deer that enters the trap laid out;
Afterwards, it becomes painful for them,
For the result of their actions is bad."

“Yonisomanasikāro,
dhammo sekhassa bhikkhuno;
Natthañño evaṁ bahukāro,
uttamatthassa pattiyā;
Yoniso padahaṁ bhikkhu,
khayaṁ dukkhassa pāpuṇe”ti.

"Wise attention,
is the quality of a trainee bhikkhu;
No other factor is as helpful,
for attaining the highest goal;
The bhikkhu who strives thoroughly,
reaches the end of suffering."
